hackathon-description-text: HackATX is a free 12-hour hackathon for high school women of all experience levels to code, learn, and make new friends. HackATX is for any high schooler who identifies as female and is interested in technology and computer science- no experience necessary.
hackathon-eligibility: Any high schooler who identifies as female.
hackathon-requirements: Build a project that reflects and addresses a social cause you and your team are passionate about! Submissions must be posted to Devpost by 7:00 pm to be considered for judging along with completing the google form on your handout.
hackathon-rules: Be nice, be respectful, be open, and have fun!
hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=6433 Champion Grandview Way, Austin, TX 78750, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: How creative is the project? Regardless of skill level, does the project show innovation and creativity?
Does the project address one UN Global Goal? Is it successful at addressing the problem?

hackathon-location-address: 6433 Champion Grandview Way, Austin, TX 78750, USA
hackathon-description-header: An all-girl's hackathon for high school women in Central Texas!
